    "Body Composition (from Scale)" : {

    },
    "Body composition values are estimates derived from published BIA equations. These equations were developed from hand-to-foot impedance measurements in specific study populations. Foot-to-foot scales (like the QN-Scale) may produce different absolute values. Use these numbers to track trends over time, not as absolute clinical measurements.\n\nStep detection accuracy depends on sensor placement and activity type. The algorithm is tuned for walking and running with the sensor at the hip/tailbone." : {

